subSubSection.paragraph:
Mesanthophora rojasii
occurs in the Chaco region in Bolivia (department of Santa Cruz ), Paraguay (departments of Alto Paraguay , Concepción and Central), as well as in Brazil , in the Pantanal region of the state of Mato Grosso do Sul and now, for the first time, reported in the Caatinga domain, in northern Minas Gerais ( Fig. 4 ) ( Cabrera 1940 , Cabrera & Dematteis 2009 , Hind 2011 ,
Roque et al . 2018
). This species occurs over limestone outcrops in xerophytic vegetation (savannah, caatinga) or in carandazal (annually flooded vegetation composed of a native palm,
Copernicia alba Morong
in Morong & Britton (1893: 246)) , the latter being closely associated with accumulation of sub-superficial carbonaceous concretions (
Silva et al. 2000
). The notable new record in northern Minas Gerais (ca. 1,500 km from Mato Grosso do Sul ) might be explained by the presence of similar limestone outcrops (
Oliveira et al. 2000
) with xerophytic vegetation in both regions ( Rizzini 1997 ) and shows its likely adaptation to Seasonally Dry Forests in South America.
